        "agent_assessment": {
          "worth_implementing": true,
          "rationale": "The finding identifies a concrete code defect in unified_ai where the agent can open multiple positions on the same symbol, violating position deduplication. The recommendation provides specific code changes: block enter_position when symbol already held, chunk exit orders under FORTRESS_MAX_ORDER_NOTIONAL_USD, and flatten oversized legacy positions. These are actionable changes in fortress-ai/trading-bot, not monitor-only or env changes.",
          "proposed_implementation": "1. In `fortress-ai/unified_ai/position_manager.py`, modify `enter_position()`: add a check at the beginning that queries `self.get_open_position(symbol)`. If a position exists, log a warning and return `None` (or raise a `PositionDeduplicationError`).\n\n2. In `fortress-ai/unified_ai/order_executor.py`, modify `exit_position()`: before placing exit orders, compute the total notional of the position. If it exceeds `FORTRESS_MAX_ORDER_NOTIONAL_USD` (from config), split the exit into multiple child orders each below the threshold. Use a loop to create orders of size `min(remaining_notional, FORTRESS_MAX_ORDER_NOTIONAL_USD)`.\n\n3. In `fortress-ai/unified_ai/legacy_flattener.py` (or create if not exists), add a function `flatten_oversized_positions()` that scans all open positions, compares their notional to `FORTRESS_MAX_ORDER_NOTIONAL_USD`, and for any exceeding, submits chunked market/limit orders to reduce to the threshold. Call this function on startup and periodically (e.g., every hour) via a scheduled task.\n\n4. In `fortress-ai/config/default.yaml`, ensure `FORTRESS_MAX_ORDER_NOTIONAL_USD` is defined (e.g., 50000). Add a new config key `POSITION_DEDUPLICATION_ENABLED: true` to gate the enter_position block.\n\n5. Add unit tests in `tests/unified_ai/test_position_deduplication.py` covering: blocking duplicate entry, chunked exit order generation, and legacy flattening logic.",
