            "proposed_implementation": "1. `fortress-ai/agents/unified_ai/position_manager.py`: In `enter_position()`, add a check at the top: if `self.has_open_position(symbol)`, log warning and return `(False, 'Symbol already held')`. \n\n2. `fortress-ai/agents/unified_ai/order_executor.py`: In `exit_position()`, before submitting, compute total notional of the position. If > FORTRESS_MAX_ORDER_NOTIONAL_USD, split into child orders of size <= FORTRESS_MAX_ORDER_NOTIONAL_USD, submit sequentially. \n\n3. `fortress-ai/agents/unified_ai/startup_health.py`: Add a `flatten_legacy_positions()` function that queries current positions, compares to allowed max (1 per symbol), and for any symbol with >1 entry, submits market orders to reduce to 1 unit (or 0 if config says flatten all). Call this on agent startup after position sync. \n\n4. `fortress-ai/config/position_limits.yaml`: Ensure `max_entries_per_symbol: 1` is set and read by the position manager. If missing, add default. \n\n5. `trading-bot/core/risk_gate.py`: No changes needed\u2014pre_trade_gate remains untouched. \n\n6. Add unit tests: `tests/test_duplicate_entry_block.py` and `tests/test_exit_chunking.py`.",
