          "rationale": "The finding identifies a concrete code defect in unified_ai where the agent can stack multiple entries on the same symbol (SMH sampled 3 enters). This violates position deduplication and can lead to oversized risk. The recommendation provides specific, actionable code changes: block enter_position when symbol already held, chunk exit orders under FORTRESS_MAX_ORDER_NOTIONAL_USD, and flatten oversized legacy positions. These changes are within fortress-ai/trading-bot, are not monitor-only, and do not weaken existing risk rails.",
          "proposed_implementation": "1. **fortress-ai/unified_ai/position_manager.py**: In `enter_position()`, add a check at the top: if `self.has_position(symbol)` then log warning and return `None` (or raise).\n\n2. **fortress-ai/unified_ai/order_executor.py**: In `exit_position()`, before submitting exit order, compute notional = position_qty * current_price. If notional > FORTRESS_MAX_ORDER_NOTIONAL_USD, split into chunks of size <= FORTRESS_MAX_ORDER_NOTIONAL_USD and submit sequentially.\n\n3. **fortress-ai/unified_ai/risk_controller.py**: Add a new method `flatten_legacy_positions()` that iterates all open positions, checks if any exceed max allowed notional (e.g., via config), and calls `exit_position()` with chunking for each oversized position. Call this method at startup and periodically (e.g., every 5 min).\n\n4. **fortress-ai/config/defaults.py**: Ensure `FORTRESS_MAX_ORDER_NOTIONAL_USD` is defined (e.g., 50000).\n\n5. **fortress-ai/unified_ai/tests/test_position_manager.py**: Add unit test for duplicate entry blocking.\n\n6. **fortress-ai/unified_ai/tests/test_order_executor.py**: Add unit test for chunked exits.",
